## API routes

All routes below are mounted under `/route/reports` and require authentication (`authMiddleware`) unless noted.

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `POST` | `/report` | Submit a new report (before/after photo + video via multipart form). Runs duplicate-hash check, uploads media to Cloudinary, runs verification, awards points, updates streak. |
| `GET` | `/mySubmissions` | Returns the logged-in user's own reports. |
| `GET` | `/dashboard` | Returns the logged-in user's stats (points, city rank, verified count, streak) plus a community-wide recent activity feed. |
| `GET` | `/leaderboard` | Returns the logged-in user's data for leaderboard display. |

### Report fields (multipart/form-data)

- `title` (string, required)
- `category` (string, required — one of: Garbage dump, Overflowing bin, Open drainage / sewage, Construction debris, Stagnant water, Plastic waste, Other)
- `description` (string, required)
- `landmark` (string, optional)
- `location` (JSON string — `{ type: "Point", coordinates: [lng, lat] }`)
- `beforePhoto` (file, required)
- `afterPhoto` (file, required)
- `video` (file, required)

## Models

**User**: `firstName`, `lastName`, `email`, `hashPassword`, `city`, `points`, `badges`, `streak`, `lastReportDate`

**Report**: `userId`, `title`, `category`, `description`, `beforePhotoUrl`, `afterPhotoUrl`, `videoUrl`, `beforePhotoHash`, `afterPhotoHash`, `location` (GeoJSON Point), `landmark`, `status` (`AI Verifying` / `Verified` / `Partial Match` / `Rejected`), `trustScore`, `pointsAwarded`, `createdAt`

## Security notes

- Cloudinary credentials and JWT secret must live in `.env`, never hardcoded in source.
- If a secret was ever committed to git history, rotate it in the provider dashboard even after removing it from the file.
